1
00:00:05,340 --> 00:00:07,700
Okay. What's your dream?

2
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:11,420
My dream is to fly in the sky!

3
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:14,360
Why do you want to fly?

4
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:18,020
Huh? I wonder why...
Just a feeling, I guess?

5
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:21,020
I want to be a firefighter!

6
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:23,200
Oh, so you'll stop the fires?

7
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:27,220
Yeah, I want to try
blasting out fires like whoosh!

8
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:30,560
I want to be an idol
who can sing and dance!

9
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:33,220
Keep everyone happy
with that smile.

10
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:34,220
Yeah!

11
00:00:34,220 --> 00:00:37,020
My dream is to become an astronaut.

12
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:39,520
- Oh, you're going to space?
- Yeah.

13
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:42,020
I want to be a samurai!

14
00:00:42,020 --> 00:00:44,020
A samurai?

15
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,620
Not good?

16
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:50,520
My dream is to become a hero
and beat up the bad guys.

17
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:52,240
- A hero?
- Yeah.

18
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:54,880
You might actually be
able to become one.

19
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:57,400
Wait… Don’t get serious on this.

20
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,520
I’m not actually serious about this.

21
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:01,520
R-Really?

22
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:04,360
Yeah, yeah, it was all a joke.

23
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:08,960
- I’m Sonoko Saruhashi.
- What's your dream?

24
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:11,020
- Yes?
- Excuse me.

25
00:01:11,020 --> 00:01:16,580
Principal, about the fourth graders’
special class… they turned it down.

26
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,520
Good morning, Matsui.

27
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:31,680
- Good morning.
- Is the chief off today?

28
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,080
It seems so.

29
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:37,320
I guess it’s “when the boss is away”…
everyone’s taking it easy.

30
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:39,460
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

31
00:01:39,460 --> 00:01:42,520
- Want some?
- Thanks.

32
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,520
There’s no tension at all.

33
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:49,280
Unlike you.

34
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:52,880
Why don’t you just stop?

35
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:57,020
The charred body...
that was another classmate, right?

36
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:01,380
I don’t want anything
bad to happen to you.

37
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:04,020
Shino...

38
00:02:04,020 --> 00:02:09,000
We were told not to
cover this story in the first place.

39
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,300
Do you have to go through all that
just to team up with the bullies?

40
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,020
You guys haven’t made up, right?

41
00:02:16,020 --> 00:02:19,160
They’ haven’t even apologize, right?

42
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:23,520
It’s not like I want them to
apologize now or anything.

43
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:29,020
It’s just... hard to stay quiet
and do nothing, I guess.

44
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:39,120
Besides, I don’t want
anyone else to die anymore.

45
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:41,420
Ah, that’s the last one!

46
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:46,020
- I see, classmates, huh?
- Yes.

47
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:49,020
Too perfect to be a
coincidence, you know...

48
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:51,020
So you want to investigate again?

49
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:53,520
Well... yeah, I guess so.

50
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:58,640
But, Utsumi, we announced it
as an accidental death.

51
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:01,520
You’ll need something big to overturn it.

52
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:04,800
I understand we can’t act openly.

53
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:08,520
Can I leave this to you?

54
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,520
Of course.

55
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,520
You can use those guys too.

56
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:21,020
With Kantaro gone like that,
only the three of us are left.

57
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:30,180
That means there’s someone
who hates us, right?

58
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:32,040
Yeah, probably.

59
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:35,240
Donoko...?

60
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,660
I don’t think it’s her.

61
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:41,020
If she wanted revenge,
there were plenty of chances.

62
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:51,520
Chonmage, if any of them try to approach you,
stay on guard and run at the first sign of trouble.

63
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:54,520
Got it.

64
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:01,020
I wonder if everyone’s doing well.

65
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,040
Huh?

66
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:08,520
There’s one more person
who knows about us.

67
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,520
Who?

68
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:15,020
Ms. Ohtani.

69
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:19,520
True, we can’t expect much,
but it’s worth a visit.

70
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:24,020
Yeah, maybe we’ll hear
something we forgot.

71
00:04:24,020 --> 00:04:28,020
Got it. So, have you
contacted the school?

72
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:30,520
No... not yet.

73
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:34,960
I’ll take care of that.

74
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:37,100
- See you tomorrow then.
- Yeah.

75
00:04:40,140 --> 00:04:42,680
She said she’ll arrange
the meeting for us.

76
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,520
I feel kind of awkward.

77
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:49,020
Well, it’s originally our fault anyway.

78
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:52,020
I hope Ms. Ohtani
remembers something.

79
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:54,020
- Alright, King, see you tomorrow.
- Yeah.

80
00:04:54,020 --> 00:04:57,020
- Chonmage, let’s go.
- Yeah, see you tomorrow.

81
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:08,880
My dream is to become a hero
and beat up the bad guys.

82
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:11,520
- A hero?
- Yeah.

83
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:14,020
You might actually be
able to become one.

84
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:16,360
Wait… Don’t get serious on this.

85
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:19,020
I’m not actually serious about this.

86
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:21,020
Thanks.
Alright, call the next person.

87
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,200
Yes.

88
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:25,020
I am serious.

89
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:31,020
I really think you can become a hero.

90
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:35,800
Ah... yeah...

91
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:04,160
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

92
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:10,360
Seeing it after 20 years,
It looks so small.

93
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:13,920
I’ve actually come to
quite a few of Kanon’s class.

94
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,260
Ugh… what a let down.

95
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:19,520
You should share the nostalgia.

96
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,720
Stop it!

97
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,020
Stop it!

98
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:31,520
Who’s inside there?

99
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:34,100
- Who’s inside there?
- Stop!

100
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,400
Help!

101
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,140
Who’s inside there?

102
00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:41,380
Let's go.

103
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:50,520
Feels weird coming back
here after so long.

104
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,720
I’ve been waiting for you.

105
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:13,800
You treated my friend like a thief.

106
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:16,840
Apologize.

107
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:18,360
I'm sorry.

108
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,980
- Here...
- Give it back.

109
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:38,360
Give it back, give it back.

110
00:08:39,420 --> 00:08:42,020
Give it back.

111
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:44,020
Yeah!

112
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:51,380
What the heck!
You’re just Donoko!

113
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:57,920
Please, come in.

114
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:00,340
What are you doing, idiot!

115
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:03,020
- What the heck!!
- Ouch!

116
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,400
Kanon!

117
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:10,040
- Dad? Why?
- Well…

118
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:13,020
What’s wrong?

119
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:24,840
- That’s Sonoko Saruhashi!
- Who? A celebrity?

120
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,260
- Are you real?
- It’s really her!

121
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:29,420
It really is!

122
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:33,480
Saruhashi, you’re quite famous.

123
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:37,140
Makes me proud,
being your former teacher.

124
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:38,380
Um...

125
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:43,240
Oh, right! Saruhashi,
could you spare some time next week?

126
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,260
Huh?

127
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:47,200
We’ll have a special class
for the fourth graders.

128
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:50,280
It’s the class of Kanon from Takaki’s.

129
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:54,400
The person who was coming
can’t make it and it’s a problem.

130
00:09:54,400 --> 00:10:01,020
Given your expertise as a journalist,
could you possibly teach a Japanese class?

131
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:04,420
- No...
- Please.

132
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:06,520
Please think about it.

133
00:10:07,820 --> 00:10:11,560
So, you became the principal.

134
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,520
Yes.

135
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:21,020
I’m retiring this year,
so this is my last year here.

136
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:22,460
I see.

137
00:10:23,220 --> 00:10:24,600
So?

138
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:27,520
What’s the matter?

139
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:33,520
I see... So that's what happened.

140
00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:39,020
Why did something like this happen...

141
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:43,020
Do you remember anything?

142
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:49,760
Like any troubles in this class back then...

143
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:55,860
Well, they were kids,
so minor troubles happened all the time.

144
00:10:55,860 --> 00:11:01,880
Especially Takaki and Koyama
were pretty wild.

145
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:05,020
But everyone was a good kid.

146
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,980
Ms. Ohtani.

147
00:11:12,580 --> 00:11:16,520
Was there bullying in our class?

148
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,020
Of course not.

149
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:25,020
There was no bullying in our class.

150
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:30,020
Are you sure about that memory?

151
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:34,820
Yes, of course.

152
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:43,400
I don’t have any good memories
from this school.

153
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,180
Why?

154
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:53,520
Because I was bullied.

155
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,420
Oh, I see...

156
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:12,020
I’m sorry.
I didn’t notice.

157
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:19,020
I was a failure as a teacher.

158
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:27,520
Ms. Ohtani, I...

159
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:42,520
Did I ever do anything to make
someone in this class hate me?

160
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:48,020
Even something small is fine,
if you can remember anything.

161
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:57,020
Takaki, you were popular, right?

162
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:03,020
If you don’t remember,
then I honestly don’t know.

163
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:08,520
There were no clues at all.

164
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:12,080
No, that’s not entirely true.

165
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,520
Hm?

166
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:17,520
Chonmage, let’s go.

167
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:19,520
Oh... yeah.

168
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:50,960
So, what’s the clue
you were talking about?

169
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:56,120
In that principal’s office,
the shelves had all the past yearbooks, right?

170
00:13:56,120 --> 00:14:00,660
It wasn’t there…
Our 2003 yearbook.

171
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:05,540
No wonder it felt weird.

172
00:14:05,540 --> 00:14:12,120
Why was the yearbook inside the time capsule
we buried before the graduation ceremony?

173
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:15,840
Did someone dig it up
and put it in there?

174
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:20,380
If that’s the case, the culprit
doesn’t have the yearbook now.

175
00:14:20,380 --> 00:14:25,860
- Then, maybe Ms. Ohtani...
- But she is…

176
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:29,820
She said she didn’t know
about the bullying either.

177
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:32,120
That can’t be true.

178
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:36,120
What the heck!
You’re just Donoko!

179
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,520
There’s no way she didn’t know.

180
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,380
Who is it?

181
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:01,800
- Yes?
- Um…

182
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:04,820
Takaki? Are you there?

183
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,760
This is Kobayashi.

184
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,560
Kobayashi?

185
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:11,120
Iinchou?

186
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:14,560
Ah, you’re here,
thank goodness.

187
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:17,260
- Sorry for springing this on you.
- Ah...

188
00:15:18,260 --> 00:15:20,100
Iinchou?

189
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:22,440
Haryu…?

190
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:25,120
...and Tabo!

191
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:32,580
Chonmage,
why are you flipping it over?

192
00:15:32,580 --> 00:15:34,700
This way, the cream won’t spill.

193
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,620
Oh, really.

194
00:15:36,620 --> 00:15:39,620
This place is just like
it was back then.

195
00:15:39,620 --> 00:15:41,800
So nostalgic.

196
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:45,120
Nah, it’s just rundown.

197
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:51,620
Is that so? Since it’s a paint shop,
the dirt is proof of hard work. It’s cool.

198
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:54,620
Huh? Saruhashi,
aren’t you going to eat?

199
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:58,620
I’m fine, thanks.

200
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:14,820
The reason everyone’s gathered here
is because of that yearbook, right?

201
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:21,820
When Hin, Niko and Kantaro died,

202
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:25,500
and Takaki asked about Haryu,

203
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:30,620
you can’t deny the yearbook’s
got something to do with it, right?

204
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:36,120
Hey, what happened?

205
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:39,120
What was up with that yearbook?

206
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,640
Sorry.

207
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:47,280
- We can’t tell.
- Huh?

208
00:16:49,020 --> 00:16:52,160
Because I don’t want to
drag you into it.

209
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,740
It’s fine to include me.

210
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:58,040
Because it’s something
that happened in our class.

211
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:01,120
I’m also a part of the incident.

212
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,700
Isn’t that right?

213
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:08,180
And surely,
there are ways I can help.

214
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:14,620
So I’m thinking
if there’s something I can do.

215
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:25,520
Well, somehow,
we feel the same way.

216
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:27,120
Yeah.

217
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:40,320
Sonoko, if you don’t mind,
would you like to grab a meal later?

218
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,380
Huh?

219
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:44,520
Why me?

220
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:48,740
Because you still look like
you don’t believe me.

221
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:54,920
Well, given the situation,
first, I have to get you to trust me.

222
00:17:56,160 --> 00:18:04,120
Also, we didn’t talk much as kids, so
we don’t know much about each other either.

223
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:11,620
We can’t go back to those days,
but I want to reclaim something.

224
00:18:23,820 --> 00:18:25,380
It's ready.

225
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:31,080
Why didn’t you invite
Takaki and the others?

226
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:34,820
It’s not fun eating with the bullies, right?

227
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:46,020
I couldn’t do anything.

228
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:56,660
I was class president, faking being good,
saw your bullying but acted blind.

229
00:18:56,820 --> 00:18:58,420
I’m sorry.

230
00:18:59,460 --> 00:19:03,820
You don’t have to forgive me,
but I wanted to tell you this.

231
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:09,240
Didn’t you think it might be me?

232
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,480
Hmm?

233
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:18,160
You knew about the incident and
that I was being bullied, right?

234
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,820
Yes.

235
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:24,960
If you knew about the bullying,
you’d think it was my revenge.

236
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:28,300
You’re not the kind of person
who would do something like that.

237
00:19:30,260 --> 00:19:32,700
Why do you think that?

238
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:35,620
Hmm...

239
00:19:35,620 --> 00:19:40,180
I felt like we were similar.

240
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:45,580
You’ve got no business in this case,
yet here you are.

241
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:50,820
But that’s because, bully or not,
you don’t want them to die, right?

242
00:19:52,820 --> 00:19:56,860
I feel the same way.
I don’t want them to die.

243
00:19:58,340 --> 00:20:00,200
- Excuse me!
- Yes?

244
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,200
Another beer and
premium harami, please.

245
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,080
Right away.

246
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:07,100
Alright, let’s eat.

247
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:10,960
I wonder if they’re okay?

248
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:13,320
It should be fine with Iinchou.

249
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:16,320
At least, she’s the most trustworthy.

250
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:19,420
It’s fine!

251
00:20:27,820 --> 00:20:31,320
- This place is nice.
- Thanks!

252
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:38,620
This place is named after me:
"Imakuni" offers 150 drinks

253
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:45,620
only those who try all
get the legendary 151st.

254
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:49,180
Oh, really? Why?

255
00:20:49,180 --> 00:20:53,220
Because it’s Imakuni.

256
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:55,100
Huh? Why?

257
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:58,400
Man, the school brought back
some memories.

258
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,820
Ah, you don’t feel the same way, huh.

259
00:21:00,820 --> 00:21:07,180
Ah, well... I always went there
just for my daughter.

260
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:11,340
But today, a lot of memories came back.

261
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:16,220
It almost made me cry too,
remembering everything.

262
00:21:16,220 --> 00:21:22,140
Like, I remembered the field
being huge, but it’s not, really.

263
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:27,820
We used to play soccer and dodgeball.
Those were fun times.

264
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:40,320
Surely... we were the only ones having fun.

265
00:21:48,820 --> 00:21:52,820
I mean, What does
"Too beautiful" even mean?

266
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:55,820
It sounds like they’re
blaming me a bit.

267
00:21:55,820 --> 00:22:00,820
I really hate a world that
judges people just by their looks.

268
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,140
What is it?

269
00:22:06,140 --> 00:22:11,320
Well, I feel like I finally heard
your honest feelings.

270
00:22:12,820 --> 00:22:15,320
Then, please tell me.

271
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:17,920
Your honest feelings too.

272
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,400
Huh?

273
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:24,320
You won’t tell anyone?

274
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:30,960
I... used to like Takaki.

275
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:32,320
Eh...

276
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:34,560
You didn’t know, right?

277
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:39,580
He was cool!

278
00:22:39,580 --> 00:22:41,820
He had a charismatic vibe.

279
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:45,820
Well, you probably didn’t see it that way.

280
00:22:45,820 --> 00:22:50,080
No, I can’t.
All I feel is contempt.

281
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:53,320
Good, I got to hear
another honest feeling.

282
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:55,820
What’s that supposed to mean?

283
00:22:55,820 --> 00:22:59,140
Oh, by the way,
you met Ms. Ohtani, right?

284
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:02,820
- Weren’t you asked to teach a class?
- I was.

285
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:08,820
I got contacted too,
but couldn’t go because of work that day.

286
00:23:08,820 --> 00:23:15,460
She’s retiring, and I wanted to do
something for her final time.

287
00:23:15,460 --> 00:23:19,700
You know, everyone's dreams
came from her idea.

288
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:25,060
By the way, I wonder
if that footage is still somewhere.

289
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:28,960
- Footage?
- Huh? You filmed it, right?

290
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:33,320
Everyone holding their drawing,
saying "This is what I want to be."

291
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,860
Are you really okay with that?

292
00:23:48,820 --> 00:23:50,380
Wait…

293
00:23:50,380 --> 00:23:53,320
Wasn’t it put in the time capsule?

294
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:55,620
Huh? Wasn’t it?

295
00:23:57,160 --> 00:24:02,320
I guess we should go after all.

296
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,820
- I’m home.
- Welcome back.

297
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:06,060
Hm?

298
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:10,820
- She fought with her friend.
- Ah...

299
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:27,320
Did you fight?

300
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:32,320
With that boy?

301
00:24:33,820 --> 00:24:36,280
- Ryoma.
- Hm…

302
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:43,320
Between Ryoma and you,
who was at fault?

303
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:50,320
You can't say?

304
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,780
Me.

305
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,860
I see.

306
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:03,400
Then, if you think
you were wrong, apologize.

307
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,320
And make up.

308
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:12,780
Dad, will you do the same?

309
00:25:12,780 --> 00:25:14,760
Hm?

310
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:16,820
Yeah, I will.

311
00:25:18,260 --> 00:25:20,820
I can’t do it that easily.

312
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,840
- Here you go.
- Ah.

313
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:40,740
Ah... CEO.

314
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:43,360
Call me Tabo,
that sounds gross!

315
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:46,260
- Sorry.
- Here’s this too.

316
00:25:46,260 --> 00:25:48,460
Thanks for letting me work.

317
00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:53,160
It’s not about making you work—
it’s to protect you.

318
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,960
Thanks.

319
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:59,460
I wonder if they’re okay?

320
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:01,420
Yeah...

321
00:26:02,820 --> 00:26:04,580
I don’t know.

322
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:09,460
Once this is over, let’s
talk to Ms. Ohtani again.

323
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:10,820
Talk?

324
00:26:10,820 --> 00:26:12,740
Why the yearbook disappeared,

325
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:16,460
Where’s the footage that was
supposed to be in the time capsule.

326
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:22,460
Thank you for your cooperation today.

327
00:26:22,460 --> 00:26:24,960
Thank you for having me.

328
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:30,000
Nice to meet you.

329
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:33,300
I’m Sonoko Saruhashi,
a graduate of Takatori Elementary.

330
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:37,260
- I saw you on TV!
- Me too!

331
00:26:37,260 --> 00:26:38,680
Thank you.

332
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:46,460
But when I was your age, I never imagined
I would be doing this kind of work.

333
00:26:46,460 --> 00:26:50,960
I’m sure you all will grow up
and experience lots of changes.

334
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:54,960
But there are some things
I hope never change.

335
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:59,260
Today, I came to talk
about those things with everyone.

336
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:02,580
Everyone,
you know the story 'Gongitsune,' right?

337
00:27:02,580 --> 00:27:04,260
I know it!

338
00:27:07,420 --> 00:27:10,420
“Takasato Elementary School”

339
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:20,000
“Next”

340
00:27:22,460 --> 00:27:23,300
“Next”

341
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:30,020
“Next”

342
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:39,720
“Takasato Elementary Forest”

343
00:27:40,260 --> 00:27:42,680
“Welcome to
Takasato Elementary Forest!”

344
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:49,960
“Once upon a time, there was a
mischievous fox named Gon.

345
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:52,880
Gon was always getting into mischief.

346
00:27:52,880 --> 00:28:00,620
One day, a man named Hyoju was
catching eels in the river when Gon showed up.

347
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:04,280
'Alright,
I’ll play a little prank.'

348
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:12,300
Gon, finding it amusing, playfully let the eels that
Hyoju had worked so hard to catch slip back into the river.

349
00:28:12,300 --> 00:28:16,600
Then, some time passed,
and one day...

350
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:21,260
Hyoju’s mother’s
funeral was held.

351
00:28:21,260 --> 00:28:28,020
Those eels were caught by Hyoju
to give to his sick mother.

352
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:33,060
'I shouldn’t have gone after the eels.'

353
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:37,460
'I shouldn’t have played pranks.'"

354
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:42,380
Hey, I’m just gonna
go to the restroom, okay?

355
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:45,960
“’I did something bad.'

356
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:49,960
Gon regretted what he had done."

357
00:28:55,200 --> 00:29:00,200
Takaki... Saruhashi was
locked in the storage room.

358
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,460
Do you know anything about it?

359
00:29:07,500 --> 00:29:11,460
I... didn’t lock her in!

360
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:16,460
“’That's it, I'll make it up to the eels.'

361
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:25,380
Gon secretly collected chestnuts and mushrooms daily,
leaving them at Hyoju’s house.

362
00:29:25,380 --> 00:29:30,120
One day, Hyoju spotted Gon
under the eaves.

363
00:29:31,120 --> 00:29:36,140
‘That mischievous fox, I bet
he's come to cause trouble again.’

364
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:42,260
Hyoju took out his gun
and fired with a bang.

365
00:29:42,260 --> 00:29:50,660
After the loud noise, Gon fell over,
and next to him lay many chestnuts.

366
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:58,460
'Gon, so it was you. You were the one
who always gave me chestnuts.'

367
00:29:58,460 --> 00:30:05,200
Hyoju held the motionless Gon tightly and wept.

368
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:06,960
The end.”

369
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:15,680
Everyone, what did you feel?

370
00:30:16,620 --> 00:30:21,780
If we showed kindness and
considered others' feelings,

371
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:24,780
things might be different now.

372
00:30:24,780 --> 00:30:30,580
So, I think we should be
careful every day.

373
00:30:30,580 --> 00:30:33,460
Thank you, Ms. Saruhashi.

374
00:30:33,460 --> 00:30:36,020
So, does anyone have
any questions or comments?

375
00:30:36,020 --> 00:30:37,560
Yes!

376
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:39,600
Thank you very much.

377
00:30:40,660 --> 00:30:44,260
Okay then, any other questions?

378
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:50,740
Okay, Takaki.

379
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:05,500
I don’t feel sorry for Gon.

380
00:31:06,860 --> 00:31:08,460
Huh...?

381
00:31:08,460 --> 00:31:14,460
If Gon hadn’t done bad things in the first place,
I don’t think he would have died.

382
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,960
What do you think, Dad?

383
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,120
Huh?

384
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:26,460
I want to hear your opinion, Dad.

385
00:31:26,460 --> 00:31:28,460
Um, Kanon...

386
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:52,360
Gon...

387
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,960
Why do you think he died?

388
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:06,460
He couldn’t say it.

389
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:13,020
He couldn’t say he was sorry
or express his feelings.

390
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:20,020
Because he was a fox,
he couldn’t talk to humans.

391
00:32:22,780 --> 00:32:26,220
He couldn’t properly tell his feelings.

392
00:32:28,860 --> 00:32:33,780
Of course, it’s best
to never hurt anyone.

393
00:32:35,260 --> 00:32:36,740
But...

394
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:42,880
If you’re alive, there might be
times you hurt someone.

395
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:47,080
If that happens...

396
00:32:49,620 --> 00:32:52,240
Apologize by saying sorry.

397
00:32:55,020 --> 00:33:00,940
Say you’re sorry and truly think about
the other person’s feelings.

398
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:05,060
That’s all you can do.

399
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:13,000
Because you’re human, not a fox.

400
00:33:15,860 --> 00:33:19,420
Humans can talk.

401
00:33:21,460 --> 00:33:24,460
We can have conversations with others.

402
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:30,960
We can express our feelings.

403
00:33:33,460 --> 00:33:38,420
So, I think we should let them know.

404
00:33:43,460 --> 00:33:47,820
Put your thoughts
into words clearly...

405
00:33:53,460 --> 00:34:00,000
You should say it as many times
as it takes to be understood.

406
00:34:03,460 --> 00:34:06,380
I hope you become adults like that.

407
00:34:08,460 --> 00:34:09,980
All of you.

408
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:21,180
Write down any thoughts or questions you have
after Ms. Saruhashi's talk today.

409
00:34:21,180 --> 00:34:22,960
Yes.

410
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:25,460
If there’s anything
you don’t understand, ask me.

411
00:34:25,460 --> 00:34:26,960
Yes.

412
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,340
Hey...

413
00:34:52,220 --> 00:34:53,940
What is it?

414
00:34:57,460 --> 00:35:00,460
Even though I can’t pretend
it never happened…

415
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:15,880
Maybe I was being naive,
thinking I’d be forgiven someday.

416
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:25,640
Making excuses like,
if the case is solved...

417
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:33,460
But from the start,
I should’ve done this.

418
00:35:40,180 --> 00:35:41,880
I’m sorry.

419
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:56,760
I’m really… so sorry.

420
00:36:11,260 --> 00:36:14,640
I don’t think I can forgive you right now.

421
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:22,620
So...

422
00:36:31,220 --> 00:36:35,540
Let’s put an end to this case properly.

423
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:45,940
Thank you.
It really was a wonderful lesson.

424
00:36:45,940 --> 00:36:47,220
Not at all.

425
00:36:47,220 --> 00:36:50,720
The kids were really happy too.

426
00:36:50,720 --> 00:36:54,360
Um, Ms. Ohtani,
can I talk to you for a moment?

427
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:56,960
What?

428
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:06,720
Only ours is missing…

429
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:08,720
The yearbook.

430
00:37:10,620 --> 00:37:12,220
Huh?

431
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:17,440
Oh my… you’re right.

432
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:20,040
I wonder where it went?

433
00:37:21,380 --> 00:37:23,600
Ms. Ohtani.

434
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:28,020
Do you remember
what was put in the time capsule?

435
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:31,720
Time capsule, huh...

436
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:34,420
Drawings of everyone’s future dreams.

437
00:37:34,420 --> 00:37:39,280
We also put the video we took
with those drawings in there, right?

438
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:44,420
But... it wasn’t there.

439
00:37:44,420 --> 00:37:47,720
The video… in the time capsule…

440
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:51,220
I see.

441
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:54,720
I’m sorry.

442
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:59,100
I’ve forgotten a lot of things.

443
00:37:59,100 --> 00:38:01,220
I don’t think you would forget.

444
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,220
Huh?

445
00:38:04,220 --> 00:38:06,380
Sorry...

446
00:38:06,380 --> 00:38:08,740
This might be selfish,

447
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:15,720
but to me, you aren’t someone who would
forget something so important.

448
00:38:22,220 --> 00:38:27,160
I’m the one who bullied Saruhashi.

449
00:38:30,220 --> 00:38:35,360
This must be the reason why
this incident happened.

450
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:39,220
It’s my fault.

451
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:47,920
But I have a family
and friends too...

452
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:51,220
- So we have to end this...
- I don’t know anything.

453
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:54,840
Please leave.

454
00:38:54,840 --> 00:38:57,220
- Ms. Ohtani…
- Please leave.

455
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:06,720
In the end, nothing came of it…

456
00:39:13,220 --> 00:39:14,720
Kanon.

457
00:39:37,220 --> 00:39:40,720
Looks like you got something out of it.

458
00:39:43,700 --> 00:39:46,060
“Class 6-1, 2003
‘Our Dreams’”

459
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:52,980
My dream is to become a hero
and beat up the bad guys.

460
00:39:52,980 --> 00:39:55,220
- A hero?
- Yeah.

461
00:39:55,220 --> 00:39:58,040
You might actually be
able to become one.

462
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:00,480
Wait… Don’t get serious on this.

463
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:03,540
I’m not actually serious about this.

464
00:40:03,540 --> 00:40:05,980
I’m Sonoko Saruhashi.

465
00:40:05,980 --> 00:40:09,720
So, what’s your dream?

466
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:16,600
I’m a bit different from everyone else.
It’s not really a dream, but a goal.

467
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,580
A goal?

468
00:40:18,580 --> 00:40:19,720
Yes.

469
00:40:22,580 --> 00:40:24,560
My goal is...

470
00:40:26,220 --> 00:40:34,220
To live strongly
so that this never happens again.

471
00:40:34,220 --> 00:40:36,220
Strongly...

472
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:39,720
I’m sure it will come true.

473
00:40:39,720 --> 00:40:43,400
Become strong enough
to overcome anything.

474
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:46,720
Yes.

475
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:49,660
I’m sorry.

476
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:58,220
I’m sorry...

477
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:02,840
I’m sorry...

478
00:41:07,640 --> 00:41:09,720
I’m sorry...

479
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:38,020
Hello?

480
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:40,960
This is Ohtani.

481
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:47,720
Can we stop now?

482
00:41:52,860 --> 00:41:54,720
I understand.

483
00:41:56,840 --> 00:42:05,480
Until now, I’ve lied to myself
and turned a blind eye.

484
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:14,620
Just like you said,
I dug up the time capsule.

485
00:42:20,460 --> 00:42:24,220
But I never thought they would die.

486
00:42:29,220 --> 00:42:32,220
I can’t take it anymore.

487
00:42:32,220 --> 00:42:34,720
Please.

488
00:42:36,420 --> 00:42:38,500
Please stop now.

489
00:42:43,380 --> 00:42:45,720
Understood...

490
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,720
I’m on my way.

491
00:42:49,720 --> 00:42:51,720
What’s your dream?

492
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:54,620
I want to be an idol
who can sing and dance!

493
00:42:58,220 --> 00:43:01,220
I’m definitely going to be the ace!
